author: Jacob Davey
title: Tyga & Desiigner Drop Fluorescent “Gucci Snakes” Video
text:
G.O.O.D Music affiliates Tyga and Desiigner have linked up for the colorful video for “Gucci Snakes”. The track, originally released back in September, confirmed the news that Tyga had signed for Kanye West’s imprint. Now the pair have followed up with fresh, fluorescent visuals for the track, which will probably feature on Tyga’s upcoming Bitch Im The Shit 2 mixtape.
Desiigner has kept himself proactive recently, finally dropping the official studio version of his high-octane anthem “Outlet” yesterday, which was teased in a commercial last year. Check out the track in full below.

In other music news, Lupe Fiasco has released his new album Drogas Light . Listen to it in full right here .
